1 and procedures. Due to the absence of proper scanning equipment
2 within the department of transportation and the lack of clear
3 rules for owner notification, Mila was disposed of without her
4 owner being informed. This measure seeks to address such
5 deficiencies by establishing clear directives for notification
6 and the use of scanning equipment to prevent similar occurrences
7 in the future.
8 Furthermore, the legislature recognizes that this measure
9 aligns with the intent expressed in the previous legislative
10 session through House Concurrent Resolution No. 171 and House
11 Resolution No. 150. By enacting this legislation, the
12 legislature affirms its commitment to animal welfare and
13 responsible procedures for handling lost or deceased pets.
14 Accordingly, the purpose of this Act is to:
15 (1) Require the department of transportation and each
16 county to:
17 (A) Scan any cat or dog carcass found on a state or
18 county roadway for a microchip;
19 (B) Record certain information and report that
20 information to the appropriate county animal
21 services or animal service contractors; and
