6 SECTION 3. Chapter 264, Hawaii Revised Statutes, is
7 amended by adding a new section to be appropriately designated
8 and to read as follows:
9 "§264- Microchip scanning of deceased, animals on
10 roadways. (a) The department of transportation shall:
11 (1) Scan any cat or dog carcass found on a state roadway
12 for a microchip;
13 (2) Record any microchip number or other identifying
14 information and a basic description of the animal, if
15 discernible;
16 (3) Notify the appropriate county animal services
17 contractor or animal control agency within forty-eight
18 hours of discovery; and
19 (4) When feasible, make reasonable efforts to contact the
20 registered owner of a deceased animal if microchip
21 information is obtained.
